# Copy this file and paste your real key in:
#   cp GemAPI.env.example GemAPI.env
#
# The filename is auto-discovered. Any of these work, tried in this order:
#   GemAPI.env, GeminiAPI.env, gemini.env, .env, or any other *.env here.
# Or point anywhere:  export FA_ENV_FILE=/path/to/your.env
#
# All of those are gitignored. This .example file is NOT — it must never
# contain a real key. Get a key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# A real environment variable always wins over this file, so containers and CI
# can inject the key with no file present.
My_API_Key=your_key_here

# Aliases also accepted: GEMINI_API_KEY, GOOGLE_API_KEY

# Optional overrides (safe defaults if omitted)
# FA_DATA_DIR=/absolute/path/to/pdfs
# FA_STORE_DIR=/absolute/path/to/chroma_store
# FA_PORTFOLIO_DIR=/absolute/path/to/store
# FA_LOG_LEVEL=INFO
# FA_MAIN_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# FA_FAST_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-lite
